[{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = DynamicProgramming","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#DynamicProgramming","page":"Home","title":"DynamicProgramming","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Modules = [DynamicProgramming]","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#DynamicProgramming.HJBEquation","page":"Home","title":"DynamicProgramming.HJBEquation","text":"HJBEquation\n\nType for storing a HJB Equation problem, i.e., a continuous time DP problem.\n\nCan be constructed directly by supplying:\n\nflow_returns function mapping states and controls to flow returns.\nstate_equations function mapping states and controls to drifts of endogenous state variables.\noptimal_controls function returning optimized controls as a function of the states and of ∇V, the gradient of the value function.\nstate_constraints function, returning the gradient of the value function for a choice of controls that sets drifts to zero.\nstategridsendog a tuple with an array of equally spaced gridpoints for each endogenous state variable.\nexog_shock a ContinuousTimeMarkovChain object summarizing the exogenous forcing term.\ndiscount_rate a.k.a. ρ\n\nSee also https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hamilton%E2%80%93Jacobi%E2%80%93Bellman_equation.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"}]
